    {
      "paragraph_name": "COPAU1AI",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This data structure defines the input fields for a CICS screen related to authorization processing. It contains fields for transaction name (TRNNAMEL, TRNNAMEF, TRNNAMEI), titles (TITLE01L, TITLE01F, TITLE01I, TITLE02L, TITLE02F, TITLE02I), current date and time (CURDATEL, CURDATEF, CURDATEI, CURTIMEL, CURTIMEF, CURTIMEI), card number (CARDNUML, CARDNUMF, CARDNUMI), authorization details (AUTHDTL, AUTHDTF, AUTHDTI, AUTHTML, AUTHTMF, AUTHTMI, AUTHRSPL, AUTHRSPF, AUTHRSP, AUTHRSNL, AUTHRSNF, AUTHRSNI, AUTHCDL, AUTHCDF, AUTHCDI, AUTHAMTL, AUTHAMTF, AUTHAMTI), POS entry mode (POSEMDL, POSEMDF, POSEMDI), authorization source (AUTHSRCL, AUTHSRCF, AUTHSRCI), MCC code (MCCCDL, MCCCDF, MCCCDI), card expiry (CRDEXPL, CRDEXPF, CRDEXPI), authorization type (AUTHTYPL, AUTHTYPF, AUTHTYPI), transaction ID (TRNIDL, TRNIDF, TRNIDI), authorization match (AUTHMTCL, AUTHMTCF, AUTHMTCI), authorization fraud (AUTHFRDL, AUTHFRDF, AUTHFRDI), merchant information (MERNAMEL, MERNAMEF, MERNAMEI, MERIDL, MERIDF, MERIDI, MERCITYL, MERCITYF, MERCITYI, MERSTL, MERSTF, MERSTI, MERZIPL, MERZIPF, MERZIPI), and error messages (ERRMSGL, ERRMSGF, ERRMSGI). Each field is defined with its length, format, and input/output attributes for screen display and data entry.",
